<%- include('partials/head', { title: 'about' }) %>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<div class="page" id="main-content" role="main">
<section class="lp-section">
  <div class="wrap" style="max-width:680px;">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="eyebrow">about</div>
      <h2>visibility over your renewals. that's it.</h2>
      <p>no bank linking. no auto-cancel bots. no budgeting features. just a clear view of what's renewing, when it renews, and whether you should do something about it.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:48px;">
      <h3 style="font-family:var(--body-serif);font-size:22px;margin-bottom:16px;">why we built it</h3>
      <p style="color:var(--pencil);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px;">every year, uk households overpay by an average of £308 on insurance alone. the loyalty penalty — the gap between new-customer pricing and what existing customers pay — is a £4bn tax on not switching. and it's designed to be invisible.</p>
      <p style="color:var(--pencil);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px;">auto-renewal is convenient when you want it. but most of the time, it's a mechanism for extracting more money without asking. the emails land in your inbox, you mean to deal with them, and then the date passes. that's the business model.</p>
      <p style="color:var(--pencil);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:24px;">perch. exists to make the invisible visible. one forward, one verdict. you decide what to do next.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:48px;">
      <h3 style="font-family:var(--body-serif);font-size:22px;margin-bottom:16px;">how we think about it</h3>
      <div style="display:grid;gap:20px;">
        <div style="padding:20px;border:1px solid var(--mist);border-radius:4px;background:var(--slate);">
          <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ember);font-weight:600;margin-bottom:4px;">radar, not autopilot</div>
          <div style="font-size:13.5px;color:var(--pencil);line-height:1.6;">we show you what's coming. we never touch the controls. that's not a limitation — it's the entire point of the product.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="padding:20px;border:1px solid var(--mist);border-radius:4px;background:var(--slate);">
          <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ember);font-weight:600;margin-bottom:4px;">privacy is the product</div>
          <div style="font-size:13.5px;color:var(--pencil);line-height:1.6;">your financial data stays yours. we process what you send us and nothing more. no bank connections, no data sales, no training models on your bills.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="padding:20px;border:1px solid var(--mist);border-radius:4px;background:var(--slate);">
          <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ember);font-weight:600;margin-bottom:4px;">low signal, high trust</div>
          <div style="font-size:13.5px;color:var(--pencil);line-height:1.6;">we only ask for your attention once a week. the weekly digest is 90 seconds. if we don't have something worth saying, we don't say anything.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:48px;padding-top:48px;border-top:1px solid var(--mist);">
      <h3 style="font-family:var(--body-serif);font-size:22px;margin-bottom:20px;">team</h3>
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;padding:16px;border:1px solid var(--mist);border-radius:4px;">
        <div style="width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--accent-soft);border:1px solid var(--accent-line);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;color:var(--ember);font-weight:700;font-size:16px;flex-shrink:0;">sd</div>
        <div>
          <div style="font-weight:600;">sam deakin</div>
          <div style="font-size:12.5px;color:var(--pencil);">product & engineering</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>